    <h3>From Hidden State to Logits: The Unembedding</h3>
    <p>
      The diagram above shows a probability distribution appearing at the
      output, but we have not yet said how it gets there. After the input
      tokens are processed through all <em>N</em> Transformer blocks, each
      position <em>t</em> has a final hidden state
      <strong>h</strong><sub><em>t</em></sub>&nbsp;&in;&nbsp;&reals;<sup><em>d</em></sup> —
      a rich, context-informed vector. To produce predictions over the
      vocabulary, one more step is needed: the <strong>unembedding</strong>.
    </p>
    <p>
      A learned weight matrix <em>W</em><sub>U</sub>&nbsp;&in;&nbsp;&reals;<sup>|&Vscr;|&times;<em>d</em></sup>
      projects the final hidden state to a vector of |&Vscr;| raw scores,
      one per vocabulary token. These scores are the <strong>logits</strong>.
    </p>

    <div class="formula-block">
      <p set:html={math.unembedFormula} />
      <p class="formula-block__caption" set:html={math.unembedCaption} />
    </div>

    <!-- Unembedding flow diagram -->
